  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Quantitative proteomics, exemplified by the iTRAQ method, allows researchers to measure changes in protein expression levels in response to stresses, providing valuable information about how plants react to environmental challenges (Liu et al., 2015; Zhu et al., 2018; Yang et al., 2020).",
    "In the context of plant responses to biotic stress, proteomics has proven pivotal.",
    "Studies involving Vitis species and other crops showcase the ability of proteomic analyses to identify stressresponsive proteins and uncover translational modifications like phosphorylation and ubiquitination.",
    "This information aids in understanding the intricate molecular dynamics underlying plant defense mechanisms and pathogen virulence (Mosa et al., 2017).",
    "Similarly, in the realm of abiotic stress, such as drought, proteomics reveals proteins associated with stress response in crops like wheat."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
